    "body": "@damianavila all this does is download those files and write them to the output directory?  I don't think a writer is needed for this.  Instead you could have the reveal transformer add the file contents to the `resources['outputs']` dict.\n\nFor example (somewhere in RevealHelpTransformer):\n\n```\nresources['outputs']['notes.js'] = file_contents\n```\n\nThe files writer (and what ever other writers may exist in the future, i.e. FTPWriter) should then automatically write those dependency files along with the rest of the conversion output.  Do you have a preference to either way?  In other words, the only problem with this that I can see (which might not actually be a problem for you) is that it will only write the dependencies if being written to the local machine.  Maybe another opinion is needed, @Carreau ?\n"
  },
