    "body": "> @damianavila all this does is download those files and write them to the output directory?\n\nYes, download the files and write to a specific location in the output directory.\n\n> I don't think a writer is needed for this. Instead you could have the reveal transformer add the file contents to the resources['outputs'] dict.\n> \n> For example (somewhere in RevealHelpTransformer):\n> \n> `resources['outputs']['notes.js'] = file_contents`\n\nThe idea behind this is to use the slides only with the CDN, so the user do not have to download the reveal.js library at all...\nTo support the speaker notes, we need to **serve** the notes.html and notes.js files beside the slideshow.html, so it is mandatory to download these files and write it to the local machine... \nIf I use `resources['outputs']['notes.js'] = file_contents` I need to create the file before load it to the dictionary (it can be doable inside the RevealHelpTransformer) but I don't think this is the proper place to write a file if we have writers to do that... and I have to put the `notes.js` in a specific path... (can I do it inside the dictionary?)\nAnd, last... I want the **option** to use the notes... I don't want the notes by default... it is a plus, and I think is has to be configurable, I mean electable... \n"
  },
