    "body": "> I need to create the file before load it to the dictionary\n\nYou should be able to download directly to the memory (without writing to the drive)\n\n> can I do it inside the dictionary\n\nYes, the key name gets used as a filename.\n\n> I want the option to use the notes... I don't want the notes by default... it is a plus, and I think is has to be configurable\n\nYou could add a `Bool()` traitlet to the RevealHelpTransformer and use the same command-line alias.\n\n_If this is only useful to people converting on their local machine, then the writer is okay._  **But** in the future we may have a ZipWriter ( @Carreau has already expressed interest ), FTPWriter, etc which will not know about the additional dependencies.\n"
